data.title: SERIOUS ISSUES WITH STAFF
data.text: Visited November 7, 2016. Had been out of USA on business for a week and wanted a burger. Went with my Wife and Son. Cashier who was taking orders was a complete incompetent, probably she could not spell incompetent. Had to ask in 5 different ways for a "Glass of Water", she could NOT understand what I wanted, wanted to charge me for a glass of water...? Did fill my burger order properly, I had to go back and ask for the manager to get my order filled properly. Owner here should think about hiring people older than 17 who can read and write.

data.title: 5 Guys is still "the best burger in town."
data.text: As fast food goes 5 Guys is still #1 on my list.If you are out shopping on a Saturday [like i do ] and need to grab a quick bite then go to 5 Guys have a burger ,fries and a drink before you resume your shopping.You wont be disappointed.

data.title: Always a Good Burger and Great Fries
data.text: I have never been disappointed at any Five Guys restaurant.  The burgers and fries are simply great!  That is about all they serve, but they do it well!    You order at the counter and can get a small burger (one patty) or the big burger (two patties) and then add your toppings.    Everything but the cheese is free.   They call your number when its ready and its self serve on the drinks.    No alcohol, only soft drinks.   Can get a bit messy when busy.   Table aren't cleaned often enough.

data.title: Amazing burgers
data.text:
I cant tell how good this burger is, wow!
You choose all your ingredients and the fries are better than most places. 
As an bonus you get free peanuts, so thats a nice appetizer.
Will definitely come back here.

data.title: clean , good customer services and GREAT BURGER, perfect for saturday night.
data.text: Very clean, floor, tables ,large garbage can, perfect spaces, clear lighting, open kitchen..and smiles teamwork..GREAT BURGER, POTATOES....PEANUTS, ART EXHIBITIONS FOR CHILDREN, REFILL DRINKS..

data.title: Homestyle burgers!!!
data.text: Great burgers!!!  I love that they are typical homestyle burgers.  You can get just about any topping you'd like.  The service is very good, and the staff gets you your food really quick.  The only negative (at least for me) are the french fries.  I don't care for their style of fries.....but the burger is well worth a visit!!!

data.title: Ohhh Hamburgers!
data.text: Customized burgers, hot dogs, sandwiches and fries, great variety of toppings, complimentary peanuts, cold soft drinks and very loud music. Messy environment.

data.title: Enjoying family time
data.text: We when to five guys to have some burgers and the quality is great but little pricey $$$ for a fast food service. They don't offer combos and the price of fries and soda are over $2.00.

data.title: "Great Burger"
data.text: Great Burgers wonderful Fries the help is very helpful! Just wish they had Milk Shakes would go great with the burgers and fries they get it right all the time Thank you Five Guys

data.title: Great Messy Customized Burgers
data.text:
Everybody knows the burgers are good. And complimentary peanuts are always welcome. If selecting the two-patty burger, expect a bit of a mess, but it ensures balanced flavours when you pile on the toppings. 

Can't go wrong with five guys if you don't have an hour to kill for lunch.

data.title: Great Burgers - always
data.text: The burgers - as at any Five Guys - big and juicy. Especially like the fries. They are the true reason to go in my opinion.

data.title: Free peanuts :)
data.text:
First I must say I am not a big burger and fry lover so my views might not be popular. We arrived on a Sunday afternoon and had no wait. Your choices here are burgers, hot dogs or a veggie(grilled veggies) on a bun. I really wish they had salad or even grilled chicken as a choice. I ordered my burger with onions, mushrooms and lettuce and tomatoes. The bun was mushy before I took my first bite.
If you enjoy fries,both regular and Cajun flavored, then look no further. They serve the fries in a brown bag and always load up the cup plus lots of extra fries.
Service was friendly and with a smile but probably won't go back due to the limited selection but hey, it is a burger joint and advertised as such.
Not a cheap place either, 2 burgers with small fries and small drink were $24

data.title: Whole lotta burger
data.text: Expensive for a simple burger  you get to pick your extras like raw onions pickles lettuce mayo and a large burger is actually a double and fries are great but the large fries is really enough for five guys. Don't fill up with free peanuts mistake I made

data.title: Greasy
data.text:
Not that great found the burgers greasy.
Really not much else to say, won't be going back anytime soon.

data.title: Ugh.
data.text: Revolting. Worst hamburger I've ever (partially) eaten.  The bun was steamed and soggy.  It tasted like undercooked dough.  Could not finish the hamburger - and I'm not picky.  The fries were OK.  It's a mystery that this place is still doing business.

data.title: -5 terrible. Disgusting burgers
data.text:
Might as well have a Plastic Robot preparing the Burgers, Restaurant was empty less than five customers in store.  

Ordered burgers and fries with cheese and bacon, and self serve sodas.

Order came out over cooked worst burger I have had in many years at any restaurant, çheese was just put on burger not even melted,fries  and soda were decent.

Very unhappy with the quality of food served. 

Only one person on duty until we left then another person showed up. No management visible anywhere. 

I don't care what the food costs, this was $24.00 for two people, Really Garbage. A disgrace to the hospitality industry.

I expected more from this restaurant burger chain that specializes in burgers and fries.

Never ever to return.

data.title: "High Guy" Not Here Anymore
data.text: Came with family and the service was good even though they were crowded. If you read my previous report about "High Guy", I am happy to say he was NOT here. Burgers, fries were all very good. Look forward to returning when I need more comfort food.

data.title: Good fries
data.text: Fast food. Good homburg, Good for quick lunch. If you like hamburger this is the place. They have good fries.

data.title: Five Guys - first and last visit
data.text: My son and I stopped at this restaurant in Pompano Beach.  It was the first time I have visited this restaurant and expected something sensational in the burger area.  I was pleasantly disappointed as it was just the normal choices of burgers.  The burger was good, but the wait was longer than expected.  The fries came out and everything was plopped in a bag, fries on top of the rest of the purchase.  We were eating in and found nothing to dump the fries out onto.  Don't mind getting all of the other condiments yourself, but felt it was a little too casual dining.  I wouldn't go back.

data.title: Order Taker/Cashier Was On Something
data.text: Was here April 17, 2014. Food was good, but that is not why I am writing this time. It had been about 6 weeks since we had been here. There were 3 people in our party. The "guy" taking the order was obviously HIGH on something. Could not understand what we were ordering (and yes we do speak English perfectly), had to explain various times and still could not understand what a "glass of water was". Second, our order came out to $32.17, I gave "high guy" $40.17. Simple right, he has to give me $8.oo back. Well he is standing there looking at the money I kid you not almost 5 minutes and could not figure it out. I had to say out loud, where is the Manager... Manager comes over I explain to him and he gives me correct change. Manager starts to walk away and I Have To Ask "high guy" for my receipt with my order number on it. Manager finally got it that this guy was a fruit cake and sent him elsewhere. When I look at the receipt, I notice that "high guy" had not put in our order correct. I decided it was not worth the bother and took the order as it was. I will come back in about a month and hope "high guy" is not there, if it is a screw up again I will not come back and go back to Elevation Burger from now on.
